In MSTest v4, `TestMethodAttribute` added `[CallerFilePath]` and `[CallerLineNumber]` parameters to its constructor, so passing a display name as a positional argument no longer works.

**Fix:** Use the `DisplayName` named parameter instead:

```csharp
// Before (v3)
[TestMethod("Custom display name")]
[TestMethodAttribute("Another display name")]

// After (v4)
[TestMethod(DisplayName = "Custom display name")]
[TestMethodAttribute(DisplayName = "Another display name")]
```

If you also have a **custom subclass** of `TestMethodAttribute`, you must propagate the CallerInfo parameters to the base:

```csharp
public class MyTestMethodAttribute : TestMethodAttribute
{
    public MyTestMethodAttribute(
        [CallerFilePath] string callerFilePath = "",
        [CallerLineNumber] int callerLineNumber = -1)
        : base(callerFilePath, callerLineNumber)
    {
    }
}
```

